
From https://soomfoods.com/blogs/recipes/mushroom-pasta

olive oil
2 shallots, sliced
1.5 lbs mushrooms
sherry or apple cider vinegar
2 cups stock
1.5 Tbsp tahini
1 lemon, halved and zest
1/4 cup parsley


Brown the shallots in frying pan (3-4 minutes), remove from pan.
Brown the mushrooms in batches (~5 minutes per batch), remove from pan.
Add splash of vinegar to pan, then add stock.
Simmer for a bit, then add tahini.
Allow to thicken.
Return shallots and mushrooms to pan, allow to heat through.
Whisk in lemon zest and juice and half of parsley

Serve over noodles

